revision.text:
[[ZDoom]] uses [[OpenAL]] for sound playback, and therefore supports all sound formats that OpenAL can play. This includes:
* {{wp|Audio_Interchange_File_Format|AIFF (Audio Interchange File Format)}}
* {{wp|Free_Lossless_Audio_Codec|FLAC (Free Lossless Audio Codec)}} &dagger;
* {{wp|MPEG-1_Audio_Layer_II|MP2 (MPEG-1 Audio Layer 2)}}
* {{wp|MP3|MP3 (MPEG-1 Audio Layer 3)}}
* {{wp|Ogg|Ogg Vorbis}} &dagger;
* {{wp|Opus (audio format)|Opus}}
* {{wp|Raw_audio_format|RAW (Raw audio)}}
* {{wp|WAV|WAV (Waveform Audio File Format)}}
&dagger;: These formats support using [[audio loop]]s.

In addition, ZDoom supports additional formats not directly supported by OpenAL. These include:
* {{dw|DMX}} &mdash; The Doom engine's native sound format.
* [[VOC]] &mdash; format used by many old games.
* Blood SFX &mdash; format used by [[Blood]], using a raw {{wp|Pulse-code_modulation|PCM}} lump and an associated but separate header lump, only supported in RFF [[archive format|archives]].

Furthermore, ZDoom supports several [[music format]]s only for music playback.

ZDoom does not support emulating the {{dwicon|PC_speaker_sound_effects|PC speaker|nolink=}} sound format, however.
